    • Field Detail

      • RULE_INPUT_REPLACE

        public static final int RULE_INPUT_REPLACE
        On input current value of a slot will be replaced. Other slots won't be affected. This is the same as text input on a keyboard with INSERT mode on.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • RULE_INPUT_MOVES_INPUT

        public static final int RULE_INPUT_MOVES_INPUT
        On input slot moves new value to the next slot keeping current value. This rule makes slot 'non-modifiable' (hardcoded)
        See Also:

      • TAG_DECORATION

        public static final int TAG_DECORATION
        Tag that marks a slot as a "decoration" slot. This kind of slots are only needed for visual representation of a text. "Unformatted" text should not contain decoration slots. The number itself is magical and does make no sense.
        See Also:
